          </table>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Other Upgrades -->
      <div id="other-upgrades" class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-200 shadow-sm p-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-['Plus_Jakarta_Sans'] text-[#1B3A5C] mb-4">Other Upgrades</h2>

        <ul class="space-y-4 font-['Source_Sans_3'] text-[#2D2D2D]">
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-[#E8A317] font-bold mt-0.5">▸</span>
            <div>
              <strong>Blow-out-back Pressure Gauges:</strong> Pressure gauges made for hazardous area applications have a blow-out-back type design. This feature allows for the specially designed back of the indicator to pop out under excessive pressure and prevent any possible injury or damage.
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-[#E8A317] font-bold mt-0.5">▸</span>
            <div>
              <strong>Vibration Sensors:</strong> Vibration sensors detect excessive <a href="/decanter-centrifuge-vibration/" class="text-[#1B3A5C] hover:underline">vibration of horizontal decanter centrifuges</a> to affect system shutdown in case of excessive shaking, which could indicate severe <a href="/disc-stack-centrifuge-mechanical-issues-fixes/" class="text-[#1B3A5C] hover:underline">mechanical malfunction</a>.
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-[#E8A317] font-bold mt-0.5">▸</span>
            <div>
              <strong>Bearing Temperature Monitors:</strong> Redundant safety devices that continuously monitor bearing temperatures and trigger automatic shutdown upon abnormal heat rise. These sensors are critical in explosion-proof applications where excessive heat can become an ignition source.
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-[#E8A317] font-bold mt-0.5">▸</span>
            <div>
              <strong>Pressure Relief Valves:</strong> Protect the system from overpressure events in process piping and centrifuge enclosures. These valves are designed to safely vent pressure without creating sparks or ignition sources.
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-[#E8A317] font-bold mt-0.5">▸</span>
            <div>
              <strong>Process Area Venting Systems:</strong> Prevent accumulation of flammable vapors or toxic gases in the centrifuge operating area by continuously exchanging air. These systems are especially important in enclosed spaces where vapors could reach dangerous concentration levels.
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <div class="mt-6 bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] font-['Source_Sans_3'] text-sm">
            Other redundant safety devices, such as bearing temperature monitors, pressure relief valves, process area venting systems, etc., may be recommended based on the process and operating environment. Contact Dolphin Centrifuge to discuss your specific hazardous area centrifuge requirements.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Summary -->
      <div id="summary" class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-200 shadow-sm p-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-['Plus_Jakarta_Sans'] text-[#1B3A5C] mb-4">Summary</h2>
        <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] font-['Source_Sans_3'] leading-relaxed text-lg mb-4">
          Based on the above, we can summarize that industrial centrifuges are suitable for explosion-proof classified areas with proper design considerations. Actual hazardous area specifications depend on the installation location and are governed by the appropriate regional authority.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] font-['Source_Sans_3'] leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Whether the centrifuge system is intended for a petroleum refinery, an offshore oil and gas platform, an ethanol extraction facility, or any other environment where flammable gases, vapors, or particles may be present, the correct hazardous area classification must be identified and all electrical and mechanical components must be certified to meet that standard. Dolphin Centrifuge has extensive experience designing and supplying explosion-proof centrifuge systems for all major classification standards including NEC Class 1 Div 1, Class 1 Div 2, ATEX Zone 1/2, and IECEx.
